unitsize(0.3 cm);

pair A, B, C, G, H, F, A1, B1, C1, G1, G2, G3;

A = (2,5);
B = (0,0);
C = (7,0);
G = (A + B + C)/3;
H = A + B + C;
F = (G + H)/2;
A1 = (B + C)/2;
B1 = (A + C)/2;
C1 = (A + B)/2;
G1 = (A + B1 + C1)/3;
G2 = (B + A1 + C1)/3;
G3 = (C + A1 + B1)/3;

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A1--G);
draw(B1--G);
draw(C1--G);
draw(A--G1);
draw(B--G2);
draw(C--G3);
draw(G1--G2--G3--cycle);
draw(G--F);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$G$", G, S);
label("$H$", H, SE);
label("$F$", F, S);
label("$A_1$", A1, S);
label("$B_1$", B1, NE);
label("$C_1$", C1, W);
label("$G_1$", G1, SW);
label("$G_2$", G2, SE);
label("$G_3$", G3, N);

[/asy]

Then from the formula we derived earlier,
$$AF^2 + BF^2 + CF^2 = AG_1^2 + BG_2^2 + CG_3^2 + 3FG_1^2 + 3FG_2^2 + 3FG_3^2.$$From the properties of centroids, $AG_1 = BG_2 = CG_3 = \frac{1}{3} A_1G = \frac{1}{3} BG_1 = \frac{1}{3} CG_2 = \frac{1}{3} CG_3.$  Also, note that $FG_1 = FG_2 = FG_3,$ so
$$AF^2 + BF^2 + CF^2 = AG_1^2 + BG_2^2 + CG_3^2 + 3FG_1^2 + 3FG_2^2 + 3FG_3^2 = 9AG_1^2 + 9FG_1^2 = 9A_1G^2.$$By the Euler line formula,
$$A_1G^2 = R(R - 2r),$$so
$$AF^2 + BF^2 + CF^2 = 9R(R - 2r).$$From the formula $OH^2 = 9R^2 - a^2 - b^2 - c^2,$ we can solve for $a^2 + b^2 + c^2$ to get
$$a^2 + b^2 + c^2 = 9R^2 - OH^2.$$Furthermore, from the formula $OH^2 = 9R^2 - 8r^2 - 8Rr,$ we can solve for $r^2$ to get
$$r^2 = \frac{9R^2 - OH^2}{8}.$$Substituting these equations into our previous equation, we get
$$AF^2 + BF^2 + CF^2 = 9R\left(R - 2\sqrt{\frac{9R^2 - OH^2}{8}}\right) = \boxed{\frac{9}{4}R^2 - \frac{9}{4}OH^2}.$$

